1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,960
Wanneung has a girlfriend now,
just like everyone else.

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:11,560
Excuse me, are you Wanneung?

3
00:00:11,960 --> 00:00:14,920
-You're really famous now.
-Win

4
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:17,920
The news is all over the internet
that you're living with Win.

5
00:00:17,960 --> 00:00:19,640
Because I knew from the start

6
00:00:19,640 --> 00:00:22,440
she would help me reach my dream.

7
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:25,040
I didn’t think Wanneung
would be this ruthless.

8
00:00:25,080 --> 00:00:27,160
I’d like to withdraw from this film.

9
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,760
So everything can end.

10
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:31,440
But please let Wanneung
continue in this film.

11
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:32,880
Wanneung...

12
00:00:32,920 --> 00:00:35,000
She seems very important to you.

13
00:00:53,440 --> 00:00:56,960
(20/03/2026 Day 1)

14
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:18,960
(Bangkok-Los Angeles)

15
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,880
You clearly tricked me.

16
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,960
I thought we were going on vacation.

17
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:50,720
Turns out you dragged me here to suffer.

18
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:52,600
If I knew, I wouldn’t have come with you.

19
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:55,120
What are you complaining about?

20
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,400
Nothing.

21
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:03,240
I’m not complaining at all, Win Pawee.

22
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,040
Go set up the tent over there.

23
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:24,040
Win

24
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:28,760
Win

25
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:30,440
You’re back?

26
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,520
Wanneung

27
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:34,040
Tom

28
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,640
Do you need something?

29
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,320
A fan ran into Win.

30
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:39,120
Someone secretly took photos of Win.

31
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:43,640
Is it the place you went camping with Win?

32
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:49,800
Yes. I’m going to find Win.
Will you come with me?

33
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,560
I have a meeting with P’Tong, the director.

34
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,240
I’ll go talk about Win withdrawing from the film.

35
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,640
Please hurry and bring Win back.

36
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:58,360
I’ve already rented a van.

37
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,720
Are you ready to go now?

38
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:01,720
Yes, I’m ready.

39
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:03,920
-Wanneung
-Yes?

40
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:07,120
You have to bring Win back.

41
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,440
Don’t let her run away again.

42
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:16,640
Win is the woman I love the most.

43
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,240
Even though it hurts

44
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:24,400
that she never saw me.

45
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:27,840
But I’m still glad

46
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:29,720
that she met you.

47
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:38,520
Win loves you and has sacrificed a lot for you.

48
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:43,200
Does Win know about this?

49
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:48,640
I think she’s known for a long time.

50
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:50,720
But she chose not to say anything.

51
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:51,920
And then

52
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:53,720
she acted like a good friend to me.

53
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,240
Please don’t tell Win about this.

54
00:04:58,160 --> 00:04:59,840
Just bring her back.

55
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:04,520
Okay, Tom. I’ll bring Win back.

56
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,840
-Oh my God
-Win

57
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:08,680
Be careful, the current is strong.

58
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,640
One, two.

59
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,680
How can you run off on a trip alone like this?

60
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:45,640
I won’t accept it.

61
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:54,720
Win

62
00:07:56,320 --> 00:07:57,320
Win

63
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,200
Win

64
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,120
Where are you going?

65
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:04,840
Wait for me, Win.

66
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,320
Win

67
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,720
Win

68
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:09,640
What’s wrong?

69
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:14,920
Win, you...

70
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:28,040
What did I do wrong?

71
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:32,000
Why are you mad at me?

72
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,840
Why did you run away like this?

73
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,080
If I did something wrong,

74
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,840
I’m sorry.

75
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:47,440
But can you talk to me, Win?

76
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:52,320
Win

77
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:55,120
Why are you mad at me?

78
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:56,640
Wanneung

79
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:58,560
I’m really mad at you.

80
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:04,440
What... are you mad at me for?

81
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:09,800
I’m mad you didn’t come look for me since last night.

82
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,360
Do you know I’m scared of ghosts?

83
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,000
I can’t sleep alone.

84
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:17,760
Who would dare sleep alone in a place this isolated?

85
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,600
I had to sleep alone in the car.

86
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,640
My back hurts so much.

87
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:23,720
Now that you’re here, give me a massage.

88
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,360
Right here, it hurts a lot.

89
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,240
Are you messing with me?

90
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:31,240
Win, why are you doing this?

91
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,520
Win

92
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,320
Wanneung

93
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:43,840
Can I have a hug?

94
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:50,840
Win

95
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:56,440
I missed you so much.

96
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:01,520
Why did you leave me?

97
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:07,120
So what’s wrong with you?

98
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:08,640
I’m so confused.

99
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:16,240
What’s wrong?

100
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:21,120
Why are you making that face?

101
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:24,320
-Wanneung
-Yes?

102
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:28,720
You didn’t brush your teeth, did you?

103
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:29,720
Win

104
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:35,920
Are you saying my breath smells?

105
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:39,120
I just woke up and rushed to find you.

106
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:41,120
Does it smell that bad?

107
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:45,200
-It does
-Win

108
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:47,120
Win, come here.

109
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:48,120
No way.

110
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:49,160
Win

111
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,720
Why? You smelled it earlier, didn’t you?

112
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,640
Wanneung didn’t brush her teeth.

113
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,000
Win

114
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:19,720
Is the shirt too big?

115
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,920
Yes, I’m not very confident.

116
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:25,360
Not confident about what?

117
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,920
Let me see.

118
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,600
It’s fine.

119
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:31,920
It’s really cute.

120
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,800
You’re beautiful.

121
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:35,400
You look good in anything.

122
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:44,720
Win

123
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,280
Someone might see us.

124
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:49,520
I don’t care.

125
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,840
I’ve left the industry.

126
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,640
Come here, let me hug you.

127
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,640
Do you want some coffee?

128
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,600
Yes.

129
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,000
Let’s go.

130
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:13,440
Let’s go.

131
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:19,000
This way, ma’am.

132
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:20,800
Thank you.

133
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:25,000
Please wait a moment.

134
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,320
Sure.

135
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:50,960
I’m so sleepy.

136
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:55,200
Win

137
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,880
I... have something to talk to you about.

138
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:04,720
What is it?

139
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:07,640
It’s about...

140
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:09,040
P’Waanwaan.

141
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:12,640
Don’t mention that woman’s name again.

142
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:15,120
I would never believe what she says.

143
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:20,760
And another thing,

144
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:25,120
I think I know you better than anyone.

145
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:27,920
Someone like you would never be with anyone

146
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:29,640
for personal gain, right?

147
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:34,480
Thank you, Win,

148
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,960
for trusting me.

149
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:37,400
I was really scared

150
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:39,320
that you might misunderstand me.

151
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,040
But...

152
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:46,520
if you didn’t believe
what P’Waanwaan made up,

153
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,760
then why did you run away from me?

154
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:53,560
Or is it because of the movie?

155
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:55,000
Tom

156
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:57,080
just went to talk to the director,

157
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:59,240
and told me that

158
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:01,600
you agreed to withdraw

159
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,320
so I could continue the film.

160
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:09,280
Win

161
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:12,440
Don’t pretend to be asleep, Win.

162
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:14,520
Win

163
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,920
So you’re not really asleep?

164
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,440
Win

165
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:22,720
Are you snoring?

166
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:29,600
You scared me.

167
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:53,920
What are you looking at?

168
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,840
Is something wrong?

169
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,040
So...

170
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:27,320
how are you getting back?

171
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:30,520
I’ll probably call a taxi.

172
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:31,800
My car’s still being repaired.

173
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,400
I’ll take you.

174
00:15:45,640 --> 00:15:47,120
Why are you reaching out your hand?

175
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:49,920
And why are you getting up?

176
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:52,160
I’ll help carry your bag.

177
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,680
What bag do I even have?

178
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:57,800
Didn’t you carry me from P’Waanwaan’s condo?

179
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:59,520
Or did you lose your memory?

180
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:18,040
Win

181
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,320
What is it?

182
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:22,800
Do you have another set of pajamas?

183
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,520
I don’t have any clothes.

184
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:27,320
Then what are you wearing right now?

185
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:30,840
I’m not wearing anything.

186
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:34,520
Try checking the bag.

187
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:35,720
There should be something in there.

188
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:44,240
Where?

189
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:46,360
I don’t see anything.

190
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:48,720
Win

191
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:50,720
I’m still not wearing any clothes.

192
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:52,440
Let me see.

193
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:55,040
You perv, what are you saying?

194
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,080
Someone might hear.

195
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:57,400
Win

196
00:16:57,440 --> 00:17:00,400
Win, Win, don’t, Win.

197
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:02,600
Keep it down, people might think we’re fighting.

198
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:04,280
Win

199
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:05,720
Don’t.

200
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:23,640
Win

201
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:26,120
So,

202
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:28,040
why did you run away from me?

203
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:31,200
Tell me the truth, all of it.

204
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:33,720
I won’t let you run away from me again.

205
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:47,800
I’m scared.

206
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:52,840
Scared.

207
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:54,920
What are you scared of?

208
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:58,040
I’m scared that

209
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:00,760
if I have to stay

210
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:02,560
and say goodbye to you first,

211
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:05,040
I’ll lose my resolve.

212
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:08,040
Say goodbye?

213
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:12,520
I’m going abroad for a while.

214
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,320
I’ll wait until your film is released,

215
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:19,680
and until people forget about the news,

216
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:21,120
then I’ll come back.

217
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:24,560
Where are you going? When are you leaving? And...

218
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,440
why do you have to go?

219
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:32,440
I’m going to America.

220
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:36,920
While I’m gone,

221
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:40,360
focus on your acting as much as you can.

222
00:18:40,840 --> 00:18:42,400
Study your script a lot.

223
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:45,320
If anything comes up,
you can call me anytime.

224
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:49,040
Why

225
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:53,040
would you give up
the chance to return to acting?

226
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:55,720
give up the chance to be famous again?

227
00:19:00,240 --> 00:19:03,200
I don’t care about films or fame.

228
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:09,240
The reason I came back to acting

229
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:11,640
was because of you, Wanneung.

230
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,840
And if I quit acting

231
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:20,920
so you can have the chance to become the superstar you dream of,

232
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:26,120
then I think I made the right decision.

233
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,320
Win

234
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:33,520
you don’t have to do that much for me.

235
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:36,640
I do, Wanneung.

236
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:39,960
Why?

237
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,720
Because I love you.

238
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:04,840
I can do anything for the one I love.

239
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:17,640
Win

240
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:55,640
I will withdraw from this film.

241
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:58,160
And let Wanneung take my place
as the female lead with Win.

242
00:20:58,160 --> 00:21:00,120
I can’t decide this on my own.

243
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:01,480
I need to talk to the investors first.

244
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:02,800
The investors said

245
00:21:47,457 --> 00:21:48,657
Wanneung

246
00:21:50,697 --> 00:21:52,537
You just got back from your trip.

247
00:21:52,537 --> 00:21:54,057
Why do you look like that?

248
00:21:56,057 --> 00:21:57,657
What’s wrong? Are you sick?

249
00:22:02,537 --> 00:22:03,857
No.

250
00:22:09,697 --> 00:22:10,937
Then what’s wrong?

251
00:22:18,137 --> 00:22:20,617
You won’t be here tomorrow,

252
00:22:20,617 --> 00:22:22,657
I’m going to feel so lonely.

253
00:22:25,217 --> 00:22:26,457
Tomorrow...

254
00:22:28,097 --> 00:22:29,417
my flight is at 1 a.m.,

255
00:22:29,457 --> 00:22:31,137
so I have to go to the airport tonight.

256
00:22:36,097 --> 00:22:37,457
That’s right.

257
00:22:38,497 --> 00:22:39,497
Win

258
00:22:39,537 --> 00:22:41,257
Can you not go?

259
00:22:41,297 --> 00:22:43,217
Don’t leave me.

260
00:22:43,257 --> 00:22:44,537
Win

261
00:22:45,017 --> 00:22:47,577
Come on, don’t be like this.

262
00:22:48,217 --> 00:22:49,857
I told you, I won’t be gone long.

263
00:22:51,737 --> 00:22:54,897
I already miss you after just one day,

264
00:22:54,937 --> 00:22:57,017
and now you’re leaving me alone

265
00:22:57,017 --> 00:22:59,417
with all those sharks in this industry?

266
00:22:59,457 --> 00:23:01,897
You said it yourself, this industry
isn’t easy. Without you,

267
00:23:01,897 --> 00:23:04,337
how am I supposed to fight them?

268
00:23:07,457 --> 00:23:09,137
And if I mess up my acting,

269
00:23:09,137 --> 00:23:10,737
and the director scolds me,
who will teach me?

270
00:23:10,777 --> 00:23:13,257
Who’s going to coach my acting?
I’m not confident at all.

271
00:23:13,297 --> 00:23:15,657
I want you by my side,
pushing me, comforting me,

272
00:23:15,697 --> 00:23:17,497
encouraging me, supporting me,

273
00:23:17,537 --> 00:23:20,057
staying beside me, teaching me, you...

274
00:23:36,737 --> 00:23:38,057
Tom

275
00:23:39,337 --> 00:23:40,537
How did you get here?

276
00:23:41,537 --> 00:23:42,857
Wanneung called me

277
00:23:43,297 --> 00:23:45,937
and asked me to talk to you
so you wouldn’t go to America.

278
00:23:48,337 --> 00:23:50,457
You even called for backup?

279
00:23:52,337 --> 00:23:54,857
I just don’t want you to go.

280
00:23:56,337 --> 00:23:57,337
Win

281
00:23:57,737 --> 00:23:59,297
Are you sure

282
00:23:59,297 --> 00:24:00,337
about going?

283
00:24:01,337 --> 00:24:02,337
Tom

284
00:24:02,457 --> 00:24:04,537
you know what I’m like.

285
00:24:04,817 --> 00:24:07,257
Once I’ve decided, I don’t change my mind.

286
00:24:09,337 --> 00:24:10,937
I know everyone’s worried,

287
00:24:13,617 --> 00:24:15,137
but I’ve thought it through.

288
00:24:16,777 --> 00:24:17,777
So,

289
00:24:18,217 --> 00:24:19,497
what time is your flight?

290
00:24:19,537 --> 00:24:20,537
1 a.m.

291
00:24:24,937 --> 00:24:26,857
Then give me until 7 p.m.

292
00:24:27,937 --> 00:24:30,337
Maybe something will make you
change your mind.

293
00:24:30,617 --> 00:24:31,617
Like what?

294
00:25:00,137 --> 00:25:01,217
Tom

295
00:25:01,257 --> 00:25:02,857
If you have something to say, just say it.

296
00:25:07,217 --> 00:25:08,217
Hello?

297
00:25:10,977 --> 00:25:12,017
Okay, okay.

298
00:25:12,017 --> 00:25:13,337
I’ll go right now.

299
00:25:15,417 --> 00:25:16,737
Win, Wanneung,

300
00:25:16,977 --> 00:25:18,137
we have to go now.

301
00:25:18,457 --> 00:25:19,537
Where are we going?

302
00:25:25,817 --> 00:25:27,257
If you’ve seen the news,

303
00:25:27,297 --> 00:25:30,217
Win and Wanneung are trending right now.

304
00:25:31,137 --> 00:25:33,257
So I have a proposal.

305
00:25:34,697 --> 00:25:36,137
I will withdraw from this film.

306
00:25:36,137 --> 00:25:39,137
And let Wanneung take my place
as the female lead with Win.

307
00:25:39,137 --> 00:25:41,457
That’s not possible.

308
00:25:41,937 --> 00:25:43,017
Casting a newcomer

309
00:25:43,057 --> 00:25:45,857
to act with Win would
make the film lose money.

310
00:25:45,937 --> 00:25:48,537
I understand, but for the next film,

311
00:25:48,937 --> 00:25:52,057
I’ll take the role as the female lead.

312
00:25:53,537 --> 00:25:55,937
You want to launch a new actor, right?

313
00:25:56,417 --> 00:25:59,217
If I act alongside him,

314
00:26:00,097 --> 00:26:01,217
an offer like this

315
00:26:01,257 --> 00:26:02,737
isn’t bad at all.

316
00:26:03,857 --> 00:26:05,817
I can’t decide this on my own.

317
00:26:05,817 --> 00:26:07,337
I need to talk to the investors first.

318
00:26:08,417 --> 00:26:10,657
But you only have one hour.

319
00:26:10,697 --> 00:26:12,217
If it takes any longer,

320
00:26:12,257 --> 00:26:14,137
Win will be flying to America.

321
00:26:21,257 --> 00:26:23,417
-Hello
-We have an appointment with P’Tong.

322
00:26:23,457 --> 00:26:24,657
Please come in.

323
00:26:39,457 --> 00:26:40,617
Hello, P’Tong.

324
00:26:40,657 --> 00:26:41,737
Hello.

325
00:26:54,457 --> 00:26:55,457
Hello.

326
00:26:56,617 --> 00:26:57,657
Yes.

327
00:26:58,217 --> 00:27:00,737
You made up your mind, right?

328
00:27:14,017 --> 00:27:15,337
The investors said

329
00:27:18,457 --> 00:27:19,497
it’s a deal.

330
00:27:19,897 --> 00:27:21,217
Win

331
00:27:25,137 --> 00:27:27,537
Wait, wait, wait.

332
00:27:27,937 --> 00:27:29,537
But... the investors said

333
00:27:29,577 --> 00:27:31,057
this is the last time.

334
00:27:31,057 --> 00:27:33,777
There can’t be any more casting changes.

335
00:27:33,817 --> 00:27:35,137
You have to promise me first.

336
00:27:35,737 --> 00:27:36,857
Yes.

337
00:27:37,257 --> 00:27:38,777
Wanneung and I promise

338
00:27:38,817 --> 00:27:40,897
we’ll both give it our all.

339
00:27:41,537 --> 00:27:43,217
We definitely will.

340
00:27:43,537 --> 00:27:44,537
-Mm
-Yes

341
00:27:52,137 --> 00:27:53,137
Tom

342
00:27:53,177 --> 00:27:55,137
I’m going to be the female lead.

343
00:27:55,177 --> 00:27:57,257
The female lead with Win.

344
00:27:57,337 --> 00:27:58,457
Yes!

345
00:28:00,537 --> 00:28:01,857
Win

346
00:28:02,137 --> 00:28:03,137
Win

347
00:28:04,617 --> 00:28:06,257
We’re going to act together.

348
00:28:12,417 --> 00:28:14,257
Cheers!

349
00:28:19,337 --> 00:28:20,537
Wanneung

350
00:28:20,617 --> 00:28:22,697
Drink slowly, or you’ll get drunk again.

351
00:28:22,737 --> 00:28:24,257
But it’s so good.

352
00:28:24,337 --> 00:28:25,617
Thank you, Tom,

353
00:28:25,657 --> 00:28:27,057
for the wine.

354
00:28:27,057 --> 00:28:28,097
It tastes great.

355
00:28:28,137 --> 00:28:30,137
The food looks delicious too.

356
00:28:31,537 --> 00:28:33,257
A toast to the new rising superstar.

357
00:28:33,297 --> 00:28:34,737
We have to go all out.

358
00:28:35,337 --> 00:28:37,137
Then shall we eat?

359
00:28:49,137 --> 00:28:50,177
Hello?

360
00:28:53,457 --> 00:28:54,897
Can’t you walk in yourself?

361
00:28:54,897 --> 00:28:57,137
Why do I have to go out and get you?

362
00:29:07,537 --> 00:29:09,497
We have a guest.

363
00:29:09,537 --> 00:29:11,337
I’ll go get them.

364
00:29:13,737 --> 00:29:14,737
Who is it?

365
00:29:16,817 --> 00:29:17,817
Who’s here?

366
00:29:18,777 --> 00:29:19,817
Probably Meedee.

367
00:29:20,337 --> 00:29:21,377
Tom

368
00:29:21,617 --> 00:29:22,897
Is this how you want it?

369
00:29:22,937 --> 00:29:23,937
How would I know?

370
00:29:23,977 --> 00:29:25,657
That’s enough, stop arguing.

371
00:29:25,697 --> 00:29:27,817
Let’s eat.

372
00:29:27,817 --> 00:29:29,217
-Right, Wanneung?
-I’ll serve you.

373
00:29:29,257 --> 00:29:30,257
Tom, stop it.

374
00:29:30,257 --> 00:29:31,417
Here you go.

375
00:29:31,457 --> 00:29:32,537
Thank you.

376
00:29:34,897 --> 00:29:35,897
Meedee

377
00:29:35,937 --> 00:29:37,337
How did you get here?

378
00:29:39,297 --> 00:29:42,097
My dad’s lawyer has already
handled the documents.

379
00:29:42,137 --> 00:29:43,417
Don’t forget to sign them.

380
00:29:44,097 --> 00:29:45,897
Why are there two envelopes?

381
00:29:45,937 --> 00:29:48,057
One is yours, and one is Gam’s.

382
00:29:48,137 --> 00:29:50,377
You asked me to help her, didn’t you?

383
00:29:50,977 --> 00:29:52,657
Thanks, my dear friend.

384
00:29:54,257 --> 00:29:56,017
So, is my hair straight now?

385
00:29:56,537 --> 00:29:58,817
It fits the character in the film.

386
00:30:00,217 --> 00:30:01,257
Beautiful.

387
00:30:01,337 --> 00:30:02,457
I like it.

388
00:30:04,617 --> 00:30:06,857
You’ve delivered the documents,
so you can go now.

389
00:30:08,577 --> 00:30:10,217
How can you tell me to leave?

390
00:30:10,217 --> 00:30:11,937
This is my friend’s house.

391
00:30:11,977 --> 00:30:13,417
This is Win’s house.

392
00:30:17,337 --> 00:30:18,777
You should go now.

393
00:30:19,417 --> 00:30:20,657
Fine, I’ll go.

394
00:30:21,337 --> 00:30:22,817
I’ll head back first, Wanneung.

395
00:30:22,857 --> 00:30:24,737
-Meedee
-Meedee

396
00:30:26,457 --> 00:30:27,737
Don’t leave yet.

397
00:30:27,777 --> 00:30:29,217
Stay and eat with us first.

398
00:30:29,337 --> 00:30:31,217
Yeah, stay and eat with us.

399
00:30:31,257 --> 00:30:33,417
The food at Tom’s place looks amazing.

400
00:30:39,657 --> 00:30:42,257
Then I’ll go get a chair for you.

401
00:30:42,417 --> 00:30:43,537
I’ll go with you.

402
00:31:03,697 --> 00:31:04,777
Have a seat.

403
00:31:04,977 --> 00:31:06,337
The food looks great.

404
00:31:08,017 --> 00:31:09,137
Win

405
00:31:09,737 --> 00:31:10,737
Do you think

406
00:31:11,337 --> 00:31:12,457
it’s good?

407
00:31:14,217 --> 00:31:15,897
Don’t tease them yet.

408
00:31:15,897 --> 00:31:17,177
They’ll get shy.

409
00:31:17,177 --> 00:31:18,617
Got it.

410
00:31:41,737 --> 00:31:42,937
Let’s go.

411
00:31:48,377 --> 00:31:49,417
Win

412
00:31:50,377 --> 00:31:51,537
Do you think

413
00:31:51,577 --> 00:31:53,537
May likes yoga?

414
00:31:54,217 --> 00:31:55,937
Should we give her this book?

415
00:32:13,537 --> 00:32:14,657
Everyone

416
00:32:15,177 --> 00:32:16,857
has a past, Wanneung.

417
00:32:17,937 --> 00:32:19,537
But the past is the past.

418
00:32:19,817 --> 00:32:21,457
You can’t go back.

419
00:32:38,777 --> 00:32:40,137
Be confident

420
00:32:41,017 --> 00:32:42,617
that you’re my present

421
00:32:42,737 --> 00:32:44,737
and my future.

422
00:32:57,337 --> 00:32:59,537
Tom, you like the head, right?

423
00:33:03,257 --> 00:33:04,657
Do you want it?

424
00:33:04,657 --> 00:33:05,697
-I don’t want it.
-Take it, take it.

425
00:33:05,737 --> 00:33:07,257
-Do you want it?
-Do you want the shrimp?

426
00:33:07,737 --> 00:33:08,937
You figured me out?

427
00:33:08,977 --> 00:33:11,937
No, you just look funny, so I laughed first.

428
00:33:11,977 --> 00:33:13,217
I’ll peel the shrimp for you.

429
00:33:13,257 --> 00:33:14,417
Thank you.

430
00:33:19,337 --> 00:33:21,377
I want to eat shrimp.

431
00:33:24,217 --> 00:33:25,657
Can you peel the shrimp for me?

432
00:33:34,817 --> 00:33:36,537
Can I have your shrimp fat?

433
00:33:37,617 --> 00:33:38,817
Eat your own.

434
00:33:38,857 --> 00:33:40,737
Yours looks better than mine.

435
00:33:45,257 --> 00:33:46,257
Tom

436
00:33:46,257 --> 00:33:48,057
Is your face getting red?

437
00:33:49,617 --> 00:33:51,617
You’ve had quite a few drinks.

438
00:33:51,657 --> 00:33:53,857
No, I think you ate too much shrimp.

439
00:33:53,897 --> 00:33:55,617
-Really?
-Yeah.

440
00:33:55,817 --> 00:33:57,137
Thank you.

441
00:33:57,617 --> 00:33:59,817
You’re like a shrimp-killing machine.

442
00:34:01,977 --> 00:34:04,057
When does filming start?

443
00:34:05,017 --> 00:34:06,657
In two weeks.

444
00:34:08,337 --> 00:34:09,737
Are you ready, Wanneung?

445
00:34:10,177 --> 00:34:12,417
Ready or not, I have to be now.

446
00:34:13,417 --> 00:34:14,417
May

447
00:34:14,817 --> 00:34:15,937
thank you

448
00:34:15,937 --> 00:34:17,857
for helping me get this role.

449
00:34:19,057 --> 00:34:20,817
I didn’t do it for you.

450
00:34:20,897 --> 00:34:22,257
I just

451
00:34:22,657 --> 00:34:24,737
didn’t want to act with you,

452
00:34:24,737 --> 00:34:26,457
so I chose another lead role instead.

453
00:34:26,537 --> 00:34:27,697
Hey,

454
00:34:27,737 --> 00:34:29,817
if you want to thank Wanneung
for helping you that day,

455
00:34:29,817 --> 00:34:31,137
just say it directly.

456
00:34:31,217 --> 00:34:32,497
Thanks.

457
00:34:32,537 --> 00:34:34,537
-See? You can say it.
-Hey.

458
00:34:34,937 --> 00:34:35,977
Seriously,

459
00:34:35,977 --> 00:34:37,697
with the way you talk,
how are you even a doctor?

460
00:34:37,737 --> 00:34:40,097
Because I have sharp-tongued
patients like you,

461
00:34:40,137 --> 00:34:41,937
so I have to be just as sharp.

462
00:34:41,977 --> 00:34:43,497
That’s enough.

463
00:34:43,537 --> 00:34:44,937
Stop arguing.

464
00:34:45,537 --> 00:34:46,657
May,

465
00:34:48,297 --> 00:34:50,017
you don’t have to thank me.

466
00:34:50,017 --> 00:34:51,937
I should be the one thanking you.

467
00:34:53,457 --> 00:34:55,177
Can we have another toast?

468
00:34:55,217 --> 00:34:57,577
-Sure.
-Wanneung, you’re already drunk.

469
00:34:57,977 --> 00:34:59,737
Just one more glass, Win.

470
00:35:00,057 --> 00:35:01,377
-Let’s go.
-Cheers.

471
00:35:01,417 --> 00:35:02,537
Cheers.

472
00:35:02,537 --> 00:35:04,137
Cheers.

473
00:35:11,857 --> 00:35:13,737
The stars are so beautiful tonight.

474
00:35:20,497 --> 00:35:21,937
Do you know,

475
00:35:21,977 --> 00:35:24,537
today is the happiest day for me?

476
00:35:27,137 --> 00:35:28,737
Then tonight,

477
00:35:28,737 --> 00:35:31,337
you should enjoy it as much as you can,

478
00:35:31,577 --> 00:35:32,857
because after this,

479
00:35:32,897 --> 00:35:35,537
you’ll face nothing but stress and pressure.

480
00:35:39,657 --> 00:35:40,777
Why?

481
00:35:45,057 --> 00:35:47,177
Getting up there

482
00:35:48,217 --> 00:35:49,457
is not easy.

483
00:35:51,657 --> 00:35:53,537
You have to give up a lot.

484
00:35:56,417 --> 00:35:57,817
You have to be serious and fully committed

485
00:35:57,817 --> 00:35:59,457
to your acting.

486
00:36:00,617 --> 00:36:03,137
Make it worthy of the opportunity
you’ve been given.

487
00:36:03,937 --> 00:36:05,937
And you won’t regret the result.

488
00:36:07,337 --> 00:36:09,337
Don’t scare me like that, Win.

489
00:36:10,257 --> 00:36:12,257
I’m not scaring you, I mean it.

490
00:36:15,617 --> 00:36:17,617
But I won’t leave you, Wanneung.

491
00:36:19,377 --> 00:36:22,257
We’ll hold hands like this and walk together.

492
00:36:23,457 --> 00:36:24,857
You’ll never fall,

493
00:36:24,857 --> 00:36:26,937
because I’ll always be there to support you.

494
00:36:28,817 --> 00:36:30,777
Whenever you turn back,

495
00:36:31,177 --> 00:36:32,577
you’ll find me.

496
00:36:34,057 --> 00:36:35,657
Thank you, Win.

497
00:36:38,377 --> 00:36:40,137
Do you know

498
00:36:40,177 --> 00:36:42,017
what’s the most valuable thing

499
00:36:42,017 --> 00:36:43,257
for an actor?

500
00:36:43,737 --> 00:36:44,737
What is it?

501
00:36:47,737 --> 00:36:49,457
It’s the fans who love you.

502
00:36:51,177 --> 00:36:53,937
One day, when you have fans,

503
00:36:54,137 --> 00:36:56,377
you have to love them very much, okay?

504
00:36:57,137 --> 00:36:58,857
Love them as much as they love you.

505
00:37:02,017 --> 00:37:03,137
Good.

506
00:37:04,217 --> 00:37:05,617
I get it now.

507
00:37:05,737 --> 00:37:07,817
Why you're such a big superstar.

508
00:37:07,817 --> 00:37:09,657
And why everyone loves you so much.

509
00:37:30,457 --> 00:37:31,097
- Cut.

510
00:37:31,537 --> 00:37:33,297
- The new lead can’t act at all.
- Keep it down.

511
00:37:33,297 --> 00:37:34,817
She’s Win’s favorite.

512
00:37:35,697 --> 00:37:36,697
What’s wrong?

513
00:37:36,817 --> 00:37:38,457
Someone said

514
00:37:38,457 --> 00:37:40,257
I’m just someone with connections.

515
00:38:08,480 --> 00:38:09,760
P’ Win.

516
00:38:09,760 --> 00:38:10,800
Wanneung.

517
00:38:10,800 --> 00:38:12,720
- This way, please.
- Okay.

518
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:19,600
Hey, hey.

519
00:38:20,480 --> 00:38:22,920
Can you pinch me?

520
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:24,080
Pinch.

521
00:38:24,200 --> 00:38:25,680
Why would I do that?

522
00:38:26,920 --> 00:38:29,320
I’m not dreaming, right?

523
00:38:29,520 --> 00:38:30,560
Just now,

524
00:38:30,600 --> 00:38:32,320
the staff called me.

525
00:38:32,320 --> 00:38:33,680
Wanneung.

526
00:38:33,720 --> 00:38:36,200
And invited me to the actors’ room.

527
00:38:37,200 --> 00:38:39,400
Back when I was just an extra,

528
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:42,400
no one ever talked to me like that.

529
00:38:46,360 --> 00:38:47,520
Win.

530
00:38:48,240 --> 00:38:49,360
Does it hurt?

531
00:38:49,560 --> 00:38:52,080
So was that a dream or real?

532
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:00,200
It’s real.

533
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:03,120
I’m going to be a superstar.

534
00:39:03,880 --> 00:39:05,360
Stop daydreaming.

535
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:07,120
Get yourself together and get to work.

536
00:39:09,320 --> 00:39:10,400
Are you ready?

537
00:39:12,240 --> 00:39:13,280
Ready.

538
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:24,400
Win, look at this.

539
00:39:28,200 --> 00:39:29,200
What?

540
00:39:29,600 --> 00:39:31,000
Look closely.

541
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,640
It’s just a water bottle.

542
00:39:33,680 --> 00:39:34,800
So what?

543
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:39,000
See? It has my name, Wanneung.

544
00:39:39,440 --> 00:39:42,600
I have my own water bottle now.

545
00:39:43,480 --> 00:39:45,520
You silly. Go practice your lines.

546
00:39:45,560 --> 00:39:46,880
Do you remember them yet?

547
00:39:57,040 --> 00:39:58,040
Action.

548
00:39:58,080 --> 00:40:00,680
Scene 1, take 1.

549
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:02,800
And action.

550
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:08,360
Cut.

551
00:40:09,560 --> 00:40:11,560
Wanneung, walk...

552
00:40:11,600 --> 00:40:13,200
like a normal person.

553
00:40:13,480 --> 00:40:15,120
- Oh... okay.
- Cut.

554
00:40:17,320 --> 00:40:18,560
- Easy scene.
- Ready.

555
00:40:23,080 --> 00:40:24,080
- Cut.

556
00:40:25,520 --> 00:40:26,880
So...

557
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:30,000
- Why do you look so tense?

558
00:40:31,480 --> 00:40:32,840
- Give me some spark.
- Okay.

559
00:40:32,880 --> 00:40:34,160
- P’ Tong.

560
00:40:34,640 --> 00:40:36,760
Can I talk to Wanneung for a moment?

561
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:41,920
Wanneung, what’s wrong?

562
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:45,480
I’m nervous, Win.

563
00:40:46,800 --> 00:40:48,480
Focus.

564
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:50,000
You can do it.

565
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:52,000
Like...

566
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:54,280
like when we practiced at home.

567
00:40:59,560 --> 00:41:00,680
Calm down.

568
00:41:02,880 --> 00:41:04,720
Stay with the character.

569
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:09,680
Take a deep breath.

570
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:11,400
Release.

571
00:41:14,080 --> 00:41:15,320
Do you feel better?

572
00:41:17,680 --> 00:41:18,680
Yes.

573
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:20,880
Ready?

574
00:41:21,160 --> 00:41:22,200
Ready.

575
00:41:22,960 --> 00:41:24,400
Let’s go. One more try.

576
00:41:28,280 --> 00:41:29,280
Ready.

577
00:41:30,280 --> 00:41:31,560
Last take.

578
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:32,600
Okay.

579
00:41:34,160 --> 00:41:36,200
- Actors ready.
- Yes.

580
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:38,360
- Sound.
- Sound.

581
00:41:38,400 --> 00:41:40,440
- Camera.
- Set.

582
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:42,000
And action.

583
00:41:45,760 --> 00:41:46,800
Cut.

584
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:55,800
Again.

585
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:59,000
And action.

586
00:42:01,160 --> 00:42:02,200
Cut.

587
00:42:06,160 --> 00:42:07,200
Cut.

588
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:09,960
Cut.

589
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:11,800
Cut. Cut.

590
00:42:11,840 --> 00:42:13,240
Cut. Cut.

591
00:42:13,240 --> 00:42:14,760
Cut. Cut.

592
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:16,400
Cut. Cut.

593
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:39,200
We’re definitely dropping
a lot of scenes today.

594
00:42:39,200 --> 00:42:40,960
- The new lead can’t act at all.
- Keep it down.

595
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:42,040
Don’t say it so loud.

596
00:42:42,080 --> 00:42:43,600
She’s Win’s favorite.

597
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:45,280
Big one.

598
00:42:45,680 --> 00:42:47,000
Want a big one?

599
00:43:07,480 --> 00:43:09,280
Let’s run this scene again.

600
00:43:14,480 --> 00:43:15,480
What’s wrong?

601
00:43:18,160 --> 00:43:19,200
Nothing.

602
00:43:23,160 --> 00:43:24,160
Wanneung.

603
00:43:39,360 --> 00:43:41,280
Someone said

604
00:43:41,880 --> 00:43:43,680
I’m just someone with connections.

605
00:43:58,280 --> 00:43:59,600
Take a deep breath.

606
00:44:01,400 --> 00:44:02,600
Stop crying first.

607
00:44:31,000 --> 00:44:32,080
Look.

608
00:44:33,440 --> 00:44:35,560
Everyone is doing their part

609
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:37,880
to make you look your best on screen.

610
00:44:40,280 --> 00:44:42,400
If it’s really too much, we’ll talk later.

611
00:44:43,440 --> 00:44:44,600
But if you keep being weak...

612
00:44:44,640 --> 00:44:46,000
Just sitting here crying?

613
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:50,200
Wanneung.

614
00:44:51,320 --> 00:44:53,000
This is your dream.

615
00:44:53,640 --> 00:44:55,200
Don’t give up so easily.

616
00:45:01,400 --> 00:45:02,680
I’m sorry.

617
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:04,080
I’ll do my best.

618
00:45:05,280 --> 00:45:06,280
Ready?

619
00:45:07,560 --> 00:45:08,560
Ready.

620
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:11,280
If you’re ready,

621
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:12,320
let’s go.

622
00:45:14,880 --> 00:45:17,200
Prove them wrong with your skills.

623
00:45:17,440 --> 00:45:19,600
Show everyone you’re not just
someone with connections.

624
00:45:20,080 --> 00:45:21,480
You’re a real actor.

625
00:45:23,880 --> 00:45:24,880
Go.

626
00:45:43,200 --> 00:45:44,360
Win,

627
00:45:44,360 --> 00:45:45,600
are you sleepy yet?

628
00:45:48,240 --> 00:45:49,240
Not yet.

629
00:45:49,240 --> 00:45:50,280
Why?

630
00:45:50,840 --> 00:45:52,400
Or...

631
00:45:52,400 --> 00:45:53,680
do you want to...

632
00:45:54,280 --> 00:45:55,600
Win.

633
00:45:55,640 --> 00:45:58,000
That’s not what I meant.

634
00:45:58,200 --> 00:46:00,800
I’m sore all over today.

635
00:46:02,360 --> 00:46:03,560
I just want you to help me

636
00:46:03,600 --> 00:46:05,600
practice tomorrow’s scene.

637
00:46:08,080 --> 00:46:09,080
Sure.

638
00:46:27,560 --> 00:46:29,080
And action.

639
00:46:31,400 --> 00:46:32,400
The word love

640
00:46:32,680 --> 00:46:34,080
isn’t just words.

641
00:46:34,560 --> 00:46:36,680
Because anyone can lie with words.

642
00:46:36,960 --> 00:46:39,040
Even if it’s a lie, I still want to hear it.

643
00:46:39,080 --> 00:46:41,960
You wouldn’t understand what it’s like

644
00:46:41,960 --> 00:46:43,040
to grow up alone,

645
00:46:43,080 --> 00:46:44,280
with no one to love you.

646
00:46:44,320 --> 00:46:45,600
I’m not jealous.

647
00:46:46,200 --> 00:46:47,480
I just want to know

648
00:46:48,280 --> 00:46:49,640
- No...
- Cut.

649
00:46:49,680 --> 00:46:50,880
Read the script properly first.

650
00:46:50,920 --> 00:46:52,040
Get the overall idea,

651
00:46:52,080 --> 00:46:53,600
then break it down bit by bit.

652
00:46:56,680 --> 00:46:57,680
I’m not jealous.

653
00:46:58,200 --> 00:46:59,560
I just don’t know why

654
00:46:59,560 --> 00:47:01,400
you had to walk that girl home too.

655
00:47:02,560 --> 00:47:03,560
You said

656
00:47:03,600 --> 00:47:05,600
you were too focused on the role...

657
00:47:06,560 --> 00:47:08,160
Let me talk to Wanneung first.

658
00:47:08,960 --> 00:47:10,120
Wanneung.

659
00:47:10,160 --> 00:47:12,200
Take a slow, deep breath.

660
00:47:15,880 --> 00:47:17,040
Let me see the script.

661
00:47:17,360 --> 00:47:19,200
- Right here.
- I’m not jealous.

662
00:47:19,680 --> 00:47:20,880
I just want to know why

663
00:47:20,920 --> 00:47:22,600
you had to walk that girl home too.

664
00:47:23,040 --> 00:47:25,000
And why I have to go through this again.

665
00:47:26,480 --> 00:47:28,000
I really don’t understand.

666
00:47:29,480 --> 00:47:31,280
How did you do that, May?

667
00:47:31,760 --> 00:47:33,280
Wanneung.

668
00:47:33,480 --> 00:47:35,000
You can do it too.

669
00:47:35,080 --> 00:47:36,880
Did you see her technique just now?

670
00:47:37,200 --> 00:47:38,280
I’m still amazed.

671
00:47:38,280 --> 00:47:39,880
Food support is here.

672
00:47:39,920 --> 00:47:40,920
I’ll help carry it.

673
00:47:42,880 --> 00:47:44,480
Wanneung, you’ve got this.

674
00:47:44,480 --> 00:47:46,040
Do your best, food’s waiting.

675
00:47:46,080 --> 00:47:47,800
- Okay.
- Okay.

676
00:47:49,160 --> 00:47:50,640
Watch the technique and follow it.

677
00:47:50,640 --> 00:47:51,680
I’m counting on you, May.

678
00:47:51,680 --> 00:47:52,800
Got it.

679
00:47:54,680 --> 00:47:56,360
The lines are pretty long.

680
00:47:56,400 --> 00:47:57,880
Like right now, we want to know

681
00:47:57,920 --> 00:47:58,920
why you walked her home.

682
00:47:59,680 --> 00:48:01,680
I just want to ask her—

683
00:49:05,280 --> 00:49:06,280
Cut.

684
00:49:10,160 --> 00:49:11,280
Cut the camera.

685
00:49:14,680 --> 00:49:16,080
I’ve been waiting for this.

686
00:49:16,280 --> 00:49:17,680
Great job.

687
00:49:22,880 --> 00:49:26,120
P’ Tong, how does it feel
partnering with overseas investors?

688
00:49:34,000 --> 00:49:35,600
- Wanneung.
- Yes?

689
00:49:36,400 --> 00:49:37,400
Are you nervous?

690
00:49:41,880 --> 00:49:43,120
Your hands are so cold.

691
00:49:43,160 --> 00:49:45,080
You’re not going to faint, right?

692
00:49:45,680 --> 00:49:47,840
If I faint, you have to catch me.

693
00:49:47,880 --> 00:49:49,960
Don’t let me collapse in front of the press.

694
00:49:50,000 --> 00:49:51,600
That would be so embarrassing.

695
00:49:52,320 --> 00:49:53,480
Okay.

696
00:50:10,080 --> 00:50:11,480
So cute.

697
00:50:12,560 --> 00:50:14,160
Amazing.

698
00:50:14,160 --> 00:50:15,480
Can you move a bit closer?

699
00:50:16,200 --> 00:50:18,360
- A little closer together.
- A little closer.

700
00:50:18,960 --> 00:50:20,960
- So cute.
- Give me a smile.

701
00:50:21,000 --> 00:50:22,800
Great. Beautiful.

702
00:50:23,240 --> 00:50:25,280
Lean in a bit, nice and close.

703
00:50:29,680 --> 00:50:30,800
Wanneung,

704
00:50:30,840 --> 00:50:32,280
how do you feel

705
00:50:32,280 --> 00:50:34,480
about today’s press screening?

706
00:50:34,800 --> 00:50:36,280
I’m really excited.

707
00:50:36,280 --> 00:50:38,080
It’s my very first movie.

708
00:50:38,120 --> 00:50:39,760
But I gave it my all.

709
00:50:39,800 --> 00:50:41,680
I hope everyone likes it.

710
00:50:44,960 --> 00:50:46,960
I wouldn’t be here today

711
00:50:47,000 --> 00:50:48,400
without P’ Tong giving me this chance.

712
00:50:48,440 --> 00:50:50,560
and guiding me throughout the shoot.

713
00:50:50,600 --> 00:50:52,600
And another important person

714
00:50:52,600 --> 00:50:53,600
is...

715
00:50:55,480 --> 00:50:56,600
Come on.

716
00:50:56,640 --> 00:50:58,600
- Come on.
- What do you mean?

717
00:50:58,600 --> 00:50:59,600
Win.

718
00:50:59,640 --> 00:51:01,280
who’s been such a great partner

719
00:51:01,320 --> 00:51:04,600
always supporting and encouraging me.

720
00:51:05,680 --> 00:51:08,000
- So sweet.
- That sweet, in front of the media?

721
00:51:09,480 --> 00:51:12,080
- Can you hold hands?
- Hold hands, please.

722
00:51:12,080 --> 00:51:13,440
Hands, please.

723
00:51:15,160 --> 00:51:16,880
- Ring, ring.
- Ring.

724
00:51:16,920 --> 00:51:17,920
- What ring?
- That one.

725
00:51:17,960 --> 00:51:19,440
Is that from the movie,

726
00:51:19,480 --> 00:51:21,400
or real life?

727
00:51:23,600 --> 00:51:25,280
You can get closer.

728
00:51:25,320 --> 00:51:26,880
Cheek to cheek.

729
00:51:29,280 --> 00:51:30,560
Great.

730
00:51:30,600 --> 00:51:32,360
- Closer.
- Hug more.

731
00:51:32,400 --> 00:51:33,960
- Look this way.
- This way.

732
00:51:34,000 --> 00:51:35,560
Over here, please.

733
00:51:35,960 --> 00:51:37,760
Beautiful, beautiful.

734
00:51:38,600 --> 00:51:39,600
Nice.

735
00:51:42,560 --> 00:51:44,480
I hope everyone likes it.

736
00:51:45,400 --> 00:51:46,560
They will.

737
00:51:46,600 --> 00:51:48,560
- That good at being cute.
- You two suit each other so well.

738
00:51:49,800 --> 00:51:51,920
Being able to stand here

739
00:51:51,920 --> 00:51:53,560
wasn’t easy at all.

740
00:51:53,560 --> 00:51:54,680
I had to put in

741
00:51:54,680 --> 00:51:56,080
so much effort.

742
00:51:56,080 --> 00:51:57,720
so that I wouldn’t feel

743
00:51:57,720 --> 00:51:59,760
and regret it later.

744
00:52:25,033 --> 00:52:26,033
Hey,

745
00:52:28,073 --> 00:52:30,633
you’ve watched it hundreds of times.

746
00:52:30,713 --> 00:52:31,793
Don’t you get bored?

747
00:52:31,793 --> 00:52:33,833
Not at all.

748
00:52:38,033 --> 00:52:39,833
Thank you, Win.

749
00:52:40,913 --> 00:52:43,913
If becoming a superstar is my dream,

750
00:52:43,953 --> 00:52:46,473
then you’re something even more valuable.

751
00:52:46,513 --> 00:52:49,033
I’m really lucky to have met you.

752
00:52:50,833 --> 00:52:53,553
Why are you suddenly being so sweet?

753
00:52:53,993 --> 00:52:57,033
Because I really want to thank you.

754
00:53:01,553 --> 00:53:02,673
In that case,

755
00:53:02,673 --> 00:53:04,713
I should get a reward.

756
00:53:05,233 --> 00:53:07,513
I already gave you one earlier.

757
00:53:07,513 --> 00:53:09,033
That’s not enough.

758
00:54:10,553 --> 00:54:11,833
Let me help.

759
00:54:29,033 --> 00:54:30,553
Well done.

760
00:54:35,353 --> 00:54:36,753
Are you nervous?

761
00:54:38,273 --> 00:54:39,313
Yes.

762
00:54:42,833 --> 00:54:43,833
It’s okay.

763
00:54:43,873 --> 00:54:45,033
You can do it.

764
00:54:45,073 --> 00:54:46,273
Of course.

765
00:54:49,153 --> 00:54:50,233
Take a deep breath.

766
00:54:50,353 --> 00:54:51,753
Remember what I taught you?

767
00:55:05,033 --> 00:55:06,393
How is it? Better?

768
00:55:06,513 --> 00:55:07,513
Gam.

769
00:55:07,953 --> 00:55:09,233
How did you get here?

770
00:55:09,873 --> 00:55:12,033
I came to cheer you on, Wanneung.

771
00:55:12,393 --> 00:55:13,633
Congratulations.

772
00:55:13,633 --> 00:55:14,953
Thank you.

773
00:55:15,633 --> 00:55:17,353
Congratulations, Win.

774
00:55:17,353 --> 00:55:18,553
Thank you.

775
00:55:18,633 --> 00:55:20,953
Aren’t you staying for the fan meet?

776
00:55:21,073 --> 00:55:23,073
I’ve got something else to do.

777
00:55:23,473 --> 00:55:24,913
Thank you so much.

778
00:55:24,953 --> 00:55:26,633
The flowers are beautiful.

779
00:55:51,833 --> 00:55:54,033
I thought you came to see us.

780
00:55:54,073 --> 00:55:55,993
Turns out you came for the food support.

781
00:55:56,033 --> 00:55:58,313
Want a bag to take home, Tom?

782
00:55:58,353 --> 00:56:01,153
Then I’ll take a foam box.

783
00:56:01,633 --> 00:56:04,153
Win and Wanneung’s fans won’t mind.

784
00:56:05,953 --> 00:56:07,553
Didn’t you say you had somewhere to be?

785
00:56:07,553 --> 00:56:08,913
Why are you still here?

786
00:56:09,433 --> 00:56:11,033
You’re chasing me away now?

787
00:56:11,113 --> 00:56:13,153
Afraid I’ll eat all the snacks?

788
00:56:13,993 --> 00:56:15,073
Fine, I’ll go.

789
00:56:15,353 --> 00:56:16,353
Tom.

790
00:56:17,073 --> 00:56:18,633
Can you give Gam a ride?

791
00:56:18,633 --> 00:56:20,793
It’s not safe for a pretty girl

792
00:56:20,793 --> 00:56:22,113
to go alone.

793
00:56:24,833 --> 00:56:27,193
It’s okay, I don’t want to trouble you.

794
00:56:27,233 --> 00:56:28,833
Don’t worry about it.

795
00:56:28,833 --> 00:56:31,593
Tom loves helping people,

796
00:56:31,633 --> 00:56:33,033
he’s kind,

797
00:56:33,073 --> 00:56:35,153
and... he’s single.

798
00:56:40,033 --> 00:56:41,433
Go on, Tom.

799
00:56:41,833 --> 00:56:43,153
I’ll give you a ride.

800
00:56:45,233 --> 00:56:46,313
Alright.

801
00:56:46,673 --> 00:56:47,673
I’ll go now.

802
00:56:48,713 --> 00:56:49,753
Bye-bye, Gam.

803
00:56:53,833 --> 00:56:55,393
Trying to play matchmaker?

804
00:56:55,633 --> 00:56:56,753
I’ll get you back for this.

805
00:56:59,433 --> 00:57:00,753
This way.

806
00:57:01,153 --> 00:57:02,473
I know.

807
00:57:05,833 --> 00:57:07,553
Hey, wait.

808
00:57:07,833 --> 00:57:08,873
Not you.

809
00:57:10,033 --> 00:57:13,113
- I’ll grab some food support first.
- Tom.

810
00:57:13,433 --> 00:57:14,873
Tom.

811
00:57:15,553 --> 00:57:17,553
Make it one box.

812
00:57:21,353 --> 00:57:24,353
Hello, I’m Win.

813
00:57:26,113 --> 00:57:29,433
Hello, I’m Wanneung.

814
00:57:40,113 --> 00:57:41,473
That was beautiful.

815
00:57:42,353 --> 00:57:43,633
So pretty.

816
00:58:57,313 --> 00:58:59,553
Thank you.

817
00:59:14,033 --> 00:59:15,473
Win, Wanneung.

818
00:59:15,473 --> 00:59:16,713
Win, Wanneung.

819
00:59:16,713 --> 00:59:17,993
Win, Wanneung.

820
00:59:18,033 --> 00:59:19,353
Win, Wanneung.

821
00:59:19,353 --> 00:59:20,913
Win, Wanneung.

822
00:59:20,953 --> 00:59:22,593
Win, Wanneung.

823
00:59:22,593 --> 00:59:24,233
Win, Wanneung.

824
00:59:33,713 --> 00:59:37,433
Let’s hear it for Win and Wanneung!

825
00:59:40,633 --> 00:59:42,073
Was it sweet today, everyone?

826
00:59:42,073 --> 00:59:43,353
Sweet!

827
00:59:44,033 --> 00:59:45,073
So sweet, right?

828
00:59:45,073 --> 00:59:46,313
Alright, everyone.

829
00:59:46,313 --> 00:59:48,073
Before we move on to

830
00:59:48,113 --> 00:59:49,393
the fan benefits,

831
00:59:49,433 --> 00:59:51,113
we’d like Win and Wanneung

832
00:59:51,153 --> 00:59:52,273
to say a few words

833
00:59:52,313 --> 00:59:54,153
to the fans. Please.

834
00:59:54,753 --> 00:59:55,753
Okay.

835
00:59:55,833 --> 00:59:57,793
I’d like to thank

836
00:59:57,833 --> 00:59:59,713
all the fans

837
00:59:59,753 --> 01:00:01,233
for coming to see us today.

838
01:00:01,233 --> 01:00:02,633
Thank you for loving

839
01:00:02,673 --> 01:00:04,513
and supporting us.

840
01:00:04,513 --> 01:00:06,193
I promise

841
01:00:06,233 --> 01:00:07,593
to stay dedicated

842
01:00:07,593 --> 01:00:09,513
and give my best in every work.

843
01:00:09,513 --> 01:00:11,233
so it turns out as best as possible.

844
01:00:11,513 --> 01:00:12,913
So that all the fans

845
01:00:12,953 --> 01:00:14,553
can enjoy it.

846
01:00:14,993 --> 01:00:17,153
Let’s hear it for Win.

847
01:00:19,633 --> 01:00:21,473
Alright, now let’s turn to

848
01:00:21,473 --> 01:00:23,393
Wanneung.

849
01:00:23,433 --> 01:00:24,953
Wanneung, is there anything

850
01:00:24,993 --> 01:00:26,593
you’d like to say

851
01:00:26,633 --> 01:00:27,633
to all your fans?

852
01:00:27,673 --> 01:00:28,753
Please.

853
01:00:52,193 --> 01:00:54,833
Everything that happened today

854
01:00:55,513 --> 01:00:58,033
is more than I ever dreamed of.

855
01:01:00,713 --> 01:01:03,153
Being able to stand here

856
01:01:04,153 --> 01:01:06,233
wasn’t easy at all.

857
01:01:06,913 --> 01:01:07,993
I had to put in

858
01:01:08,033 --> 01:01:09,953
so much effort.

